<Layout title="Session 112 — Tales of the Radiant Citadel" description="The party emerged from last session's cliffhanger to a deal with the **High Master** — the gargantuan Elder Brain Dragon claims to be fighting a 2,000-year">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <a href="/studio" class="text-sm text-earth hover:text-ink transition-colors mb-6 inline-block">&larr; Studio</a>

    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black leading-tight mb-2">
      Session 112
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth mb-1">Tales of the Radiant Citadel &middot; April 28, 2026</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-light mb-8">Bluetspur Expedition</p>

    <div class="prose-section text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-12 space-y-4">
      <p>
        The party emerged from last session's cliffhanger to a deal with the **High Master** — the gargantuan Elder Brain Dragon claims to be fighting a 2,000-year-stagnant civil war against another Elder Brain, the **god brain**, and offers an alliance: retrieve a &quot;thought virus&quot; from his old spawning pits and deliver it to the god brain's lair, in exchange for armies and knowledge. Virgil, hot-headed, swallowed an Illithid tadpole &quot;like an oyster shot&quot; to sample the philosophy and immediately began ceremorphosis. Sundr saved his life by **Banishing him to a harmless demiplane** — flavored as an IKEA / doctor's-waiting-room — long enough for the aberration tadpole to remain banished while the humanoid Virgil snapped back, tadpole-free. Meanwhile, Kiet (alone above ground guarding the borrowed Concordant Jewel) was conned by a wormy fish-folk seer who teleported him 60 feet outside the jewel and stole it — only for **a massive purple beam to fire from the X-marked NW mountain and shatter the jewel into thousands of pieces**, raining shards across the wasteland. The party's only way home is gone. Kiet was brought before the worm-seer's queen — a robed figure on a wooden throne whose voice was &quot;a million tiny voices&quot; and who came undone into a **swarm of worms in woman-shape**. She named **Edda the betrayer** in the prophecy, revealed that the Illithids spread to other worlds via **rats** (recontextualizing Twelve), and confirmed that the future-mind-flayers' time-travel into ancient Bluetspur is what doomed her people — descendants who became their own ancestors' destroyers. Session ended with the party flying south low and &quot;thinking small thoughts&quot; toward the spawning pits, Kiet rejoining them with **permanent mutations** (3x water requirement, tripled jump distance, knees bent backward like an ostrich) and a small mutant servant in tow.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Highlights</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm text-ink-light leading-relaxed space-y-2 mb-12 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Cold Open — Recap and the Two-Front Cliffhanger</strong> — Sam: &quot;I don't love it when you miss sessions, but I do love the session after you miss sessions. So saying — the first hour of this session, one of our characters has started a fight with the elder brain dragon, and the other one appears to be about to let the mysterious mutant aliens drive our spaceship.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The High Master's Pitch</strong> — Sam describing the dragon: &quot;There is a throbbing in your heads from the sheer weight of the psychic energy around you, and in the back of the cavern flitting into and out of the shadows, yes, is an elder brain dragon — the being that calls itself the High Master, a dragon corrupted by Illithid technology or technique.&quot; Roughly 40 feet long, tentacles twitching from the back of its skull.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Virgil Eats the Tadpole</strong> — Virgil pushes for a sample of the philosophy: &quot;What about, like, a little bit? Can we, like, push the boundary here? I have some mushroom connections.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">&quot;TPK Incoming. Holy Shit.&quot;</strong> — Initiative. Virgil, raging in self-loathing: &quot;Shut up. Shit. Shut your mouth. I'm gonna kinda go crazy, and then I'm gonna take my glaive and just try to slay this dragon right now.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr's Save — Banishment to the IKEA Demiplane</strong> — **Sundr's first action: Command** (&quot;halt&quot;) on Virgil. Wis save DC 19. Virgil saves. (Erik flagged the Aura of Protection question proactively — it doesn't apply against allies' spells.)</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Deal</strong> — Sundr renegotiates from a position of restored credibility. The terms:</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">HARD CUT — Kiet Alone with the Jewel</strong> — Sam clarifies the jewel mechanics: not properly attuned to Bluetspur. **&quot;Like the end of a rubber band held taut.&quot;** Without effort it snaps back to the Citadel. Kiet must hold a button.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Heist</strong> — Kiet hands over the door controls but won't leave the button. The seer offers to &quot;help drive.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Purple Flash</strong> — Sam: **&quot;The last thing that you are going to see in this scene is, as the jewel is reaching the point where you are no longer able to see it, a massive blast of purplish energy will emanate from the side of the largest mountain and shatter it... shatter the Concordant Jewel into thousands of pieces that rain down across the land.&quot;**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Throne Room — The Woman Who Is Worms</strong> — Kiet is led back through the mutant caverns and brought before a robed figure on a wooden throne, pallid white mask, vaguely female. She casts Tongues.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Mutation Table</strong> — Kiet, alone, no jewel, no party, on a radioactive planet. The worm-queen offers protection: a **limited and directed bombardment** of the radiant energy. It will mutate him but make him resistant. **One negative roll, one positive roll.** Permanent until Greater Restoration or higher curative magic.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Reunion on the Carpet</strong> — Party flies south on the flying carpet, low, &quot;thinking small thoughts.&quot;</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Art</h2>
    <div class="space-y-10">
      {images.map((img) => (
        <figure>
          <img
            src={img.src}
            alt={img.title}
            class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-lg"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="mt-3">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink text-sm">{img.title}</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-light mt-1">{img.caption}</p>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-cream-dark mt-16 pt-8">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3">Party</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Sundr</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Erik) — Aasimar Sorcerer</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Kiet</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Jonas) — Dragonborn Fighter</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Virgil Gemnar</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Kyle) — Goliath Barbarian</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Toven</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Max) — Druid</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Haru</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Hunter) — Kobold Paladin</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">—</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Sam (DM))</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
